Those people in sociology departments doing gender studies or whatever quoting Michael Foucault to each other are literally burning public money in an advanced wellfare scheme producing nothing of value. These fields should be completely gutted and the money given to real science

One thing I am very passionate about is completely defunding the humanities. It's obvious it's been decades now since they've been able to produce quality anything, there shouldn't be a single cent going into philosophy or literature departments. Give it all to materials science.

A pro-metabolic society means everyone is like Gene Wolfe: everyone has the "vital energy" to work a job as an engineer, edit a botanical science magazine, write novels on top of that, then play chess and practice knife throwing as sport in his free time while also reading a ton.

You can see how vital he lived life even looking at how in his suburban short stories everyone has complicated hobbies, e.g. neighborhood wives in Suzanne Delage have a club dedicated to collecting antique fabrics and quilts and casually travel by train weekly to search for them.

One of the most important things that people get from supplementing thyroid hormone Broda Barnes style is just having the energy to hold a good dayjob, play tennis on the weekend, do a hobby like making chairs woodworking in your free time, read a novel a week. You can *do* more.
